
# Clone Hero Spotify Syncronizer

This project is aimed to clone hero players, that just wanna play the songs of some Spotify playlist.




## Environment vars

To run this project, you will need to add the following environment variables to your .env

`CLIENT_ID`

`CLIENT_SECRET`

Here is the tutorial to get this values: [Getting Started with spotify for devs](https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/tutorials/getting-started)


## Running on localhost

Clone the project

```bash
  git clone https://github.com/Davi-zzz/clone-hero-spotify-syncronizer
```

Go to project dir

```bash
  cd my-project
```

Install the dependencies

```bash
  npm install
```

Start the server

```bash
  npm run start
```

